{
  "body": "A stunning vertical social-media visual poster: {{card_holder}}, holding a highly detailed {{platform}} laid flat (parallel to the camera, slightly tilted toward the viewer for depth).\n\n— The profile card (real, physical, in-focus) —\n{{card_content_summary}}\nThe card itself is rendered with photorealistic materiality — slight thickness, soft printed edge, crisp UI typography, faint catchlight on the surface. It is a real physical object held by the hand, NOT a screen.\n\n— The hologram projection (CRITICAL — the hero of the image) —\nFrom the surface of the profile card, a FULL-BODY standing 3D holographic projection of {{projection_subject}} emerges and floats above the card. The projection:\n  • is semi-transparent, with the background and the hand visible faintly through it\n  • glows softly with a {{hologram_color}}\n  • has slightly luminous edges with subtle scan-line / iridescence at the silhouette\n  • fades into thin light at the very bottom where it connects to the card surface (as if the figure is being beamed UP from the card)\n  • casts a faint colored bloom onto the card and the hand below\n  • is the largest single element in the upper portion of the frame, completely visible from head to toe\n\n— Particles & light rays —\n{{particles_density}}. Particles flow gracefully around the projection (not a chaotic snow storm), with a few brighter specks catching the {{hologram_color}}. Thin volumetric light rays connect the card surface to the hologram, suggesting the source of the projection.\n\n— Background —\n{{background}}. The background stays soft and slightly out of focus, NEVER competing with the hand + card + hologram trio. Subtle depth-of-field bokeh on background elements.\n\n— Lighting —\n{{lighting_style}}. The hand and card are crisply lit with cinematic-grade key light. The hologram's own glow contributes a secondary warm/cool ambient onto the surrounding scene.\n\n— Composition —\nVertical composition in {{aspect_ratio}} aspect ratio. The hand + card occupies roughly the lower third of the frame; the holographic projection occupies the middle and upper portion. Generous breathing space around the projection so it never touches the top edge. Slight rule-of-thirds offset for editorial feel — NOT dead-center.\n\n— Style references —\nUltra-high detail, cinematic-grade lighting, god-rays, golden glow, dreamy pastel aesthetic. Reference visual mood: high-end cosmetics ad campaigns (Glossier, Rare Beauty), dreamy idol holographic stage visuals (K-pop concept teasers), and the cinematic soft glow of films like \"Her\" (2013) and \"Blade Runner 2049\" (the holographic Joi scenes). Photoreal CGI quality, Octane / Unreal Engine 5 rendering finish.\n\n— Additional details —\n{{extra_notes}}\n\n— Strictly avoid —\n- Do NOT crop the holographic figure — full body from head to toe must be visible\n- Do NOT make the hologram fully opaque — semi-transparency is mandatory (the card surface visible behind the figure's lower portion)\n- Do NOT render the card as a phone screen or tablet — it must be a printed/material object\n- Do NOT make the hand cartoon-y or proportionally weird — it must be a beautiful real-photo-quality hand\n- Do NOT generate gibberish text on the card UI — if uncertain about specific characters, use abstract bars or simplified placeholders rather than fake glyphs\n- Do NOT clutter with too many particles, stars, lens flares, or sparkles competing for attention\n- Do NOT use rainbow neon palette unless hologram_color explicitly is the iridescent option\n- Do NOT add overlay text, watermarks, logos (other than the small native platform logo on the card itself)\n- Do NOT make the background louder than the hologram — keep depth-of-field separation\n- Do NOT use dated 2010s sci-fi UI clichés (giant glowing rings, spinning gears, blue grids) — keep the hologram aesthetic modern and refined\n- Do NOT make the projection's connection to the card look like a beam of pure white light — it should be a soft particle dissolve\n\nKeywords: holographic projection, profile card, social media poster, dreamy pastel, cinematic glow, god rays, golden hour, photoreal CGI, vertical composition, magical aesthetic, hologram girl, soft focus, premium social campaign visual",
